Near Bermuda Run / Mile Marker 179 to 182 Heading East. The Contractor for the&nbsp;I-40 Project at the Davie-Forsyth County Line is scheduled to keep one lane closed of I-40 Eastbound&nbsp;from 1 mile west of NC 801 (Exit 180) to Harper Road (Exit 182) for two weeks. The contractor will install this lane closure from Tuesday August 18th (6:00PM) thru Friday September 4th (5:00AM). This closure will alternate from a right lane closure to a left lane closure depending on work progress. These lane closures are required for the contractor to safely perform paving operations and to set traffic protection systems. This work is part of the&nbsp;continuing construction to&nbsp;replace the I-40 bridges over the Yadkin River and to widen and make improvements along I-40.&nbsp;As always this work is weather dependent and may be subject to change.
